message.content: This paper likely belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Other possible sub-categories could include Machine Learning (cs.LG), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), or Data Mining (cs.DM). The paper discusses the creation of a conversational layer over semi-structured data, which is a common problem in NLP and IR. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of QnAMaker, which is a service commonly used in the field of machine learning. The paper could also be relevant to the fields of HCI and data mining, as it deals with improving user experience and reducing traffic to human support.
